messages.content: Tell me about this dandiset. *

This Dandiset, titled "Calcium imaging in SMA and M1 of macaques" (DANDI:001174, version 0.250331.2218), contains data from a neuroscience study using calcium imaging to investigate neuronal activity in the supplementary motor area (SMA) and primary motor cortex (M1) of rhesus macaques. Here are the key details:

- **Objective:** Track the calcium activity of SMA and M1 neurons at rest and during arm reaches, focusing on neuronal coactivation, activity sequences, and cell pair synchrony.
- **Data:** In vivo calcium imaging using GCaMP6f and miniature microscopes (one-photon), with GRIN lens implants in four rhesus monkeys.
- **Contents:** NWB files with imaging data, segmented neurons, coactivation analyses, and relevant metadata.
- **Species:** Macaca mulatta (Rhesus monkey)
- **Sample Size:** 4 subjects, 45 NWB files, nearly 688 GB total size
- **Techniques:** One-photon microscopy, microendoscope imaging, calcium sensors, behavioral task monitoring (arm reaching task)
- **Related Resources:**
    - [Preprint: MICROENDOSCOPIC CALCIUM IMAGING IN SUPPLEMENTARY MOTOR AREA AND PRIMARY MOTOR CORTEX OF RHESUS MACAQUES AT REST AND DURING ARM MOVEMENT](https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2024.06.20.599918v3)
    - [Descriptors of calcium cell activities on Zenodo](https://zenodo.org/uploads/14727695)

**Citation:**  
Galvan, Adriana et al. (2025) Calcium imaging in SMA and M1 of macaques (Version 0.250331.2218) [Data set]. DANDI Archive. https://doi.org/10.48324/dandi.001174/0.250331.2218

The file sub-Q/sub-Q_ophys.nwb contains the following primary data types and associated metadata:

### 1. Imaging Data (Raw Calcium Imaging)
- **Type:** OnePhotonSeries (raw imaging frames)
- **Shape:** (6041 frames, 320 x 200 pixels), dtype=uint16
- **Frame rate:** ~10.01 Hz
- **Description:** Miniscope imaging data (fluorescence)
- **Imaging Plane:** Miniscope, 475 nm excitation, manufactured by Inscopix, Inc.

### 2. Processed Calcium Signals
- **Type:** Fluorescence and Event Amplitude for segmented ROIs
    - **Fluorescence (RoiResponseSeries):**
        - Processed fluorescence traces for each ROI (shape: 6041 x 40; float32)
        - Linked to cell segmentation (ROIs) via PlaneSegmentation
    - **EventAmplitude (RoiResponseSeries):**
        - Amplitude of events, likely representing inferred neural activity (shape: 6041 x 40; float64)
        - Associated with each segmented cell (ROI)
- **Metadata:** Each ROI is linked to an image mask showing its spatial footprint. All ROIs are traceable to their parent imaging plane, segmentation, and acquisition parameters.

### 3. ROI Segmentation Data
- **Type:** PlaneSegmentation (under ImageSegmentation)
    - Contains spatial definitions (image_mask) for each of the 40 ROIs (cells).
    - Reference to imaging and device metadata.

### 4. Subject/Session Metadata
- Subject: ID Q, Female, Macaca mulatta, Age: P5Y (5 years postnatal)
- Session: “Calcium imaging in SMA during the spontaneous condition”
- Date: 2022-09-15T13:16:33

### 5. Device and Imaging Metadata
- Device: Miniscope (NVista3, Inscopix, Inc.)
- Excitation wavelength: 475 nm
- Imaging rate: 10.01 Hz

---

#### Summary Table

| Data Type           | Description                                   | Dimensions                  | Notes                              |
|---------------------|-----------------------------------------------|-----------------------------|------------------------------------|
| OnePhotonSeries     | Raw imaging video (miniscope)                 | (6041, 320, 200)            | Fluorescence, 10 Hz                |
| Fluorescence        | Traces from segmented ROIs                    | (6041, 40)                  | Processed ΔF/F, each cell          |
| EventAmplitude      | Events detected in ROIs                       | (6041, 40)                  | Putative neural spikes/events      |
| ImageSegmentation   | Spatial masks of each cell (ROI)              | 40 ROIs                     | Each ROI with image mask           |
| Subject/Session     | Metadata about experiment and animal          | -                           | ID, species, sex, age, date/time   |
